The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bangla slump to 121/6
                                                     Bangla slump to 121/6
                  West Indies players celebrate the fall of a Bangladesh wicket in Kingstown on Friday                     
	Kingstown: A new-look West Indies seam attack dismissed the Bangladesh top order on Friday as the visitors slumped to 121 for six at lunch on the second day of the first Test at Arnos Vale on Friday.         
	Tino Best claimed two for 30, Dave Bernard took two for 26 and there was a wicket apiece for Darren Sammy and Kemar Roach.         
	Bangladesh began day two on 42 for no loss after a rain-curtailed opening day.         
	Junaid Siddique and Raqibul Hasan shared a restorative stand of 30 for the third wicket.           (AP)                                                                                                                   
